verbose_text: Then freshly prepared Milstein catalyst in THF (0.5 mL), made by reacting the precursor ([2-(di-tert-butylphosphinomethyl)-6-(diethylaminomethyl) pyridine] ruthenium (II) chlorocarbonyl hydride) (0.025 mmol, 12.2 mg, 0.5 mol%) with tBuOK (0.025 mmol, 2.8 mg, 0.5 mol%) was added in a glovebox into the Schlenk flask dropwise via a syringe and the reaction was stirred under nitrogen at ambient temperature (or -30 degreesC for 2 d) overnight.
